{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17647071","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17647071"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:39:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:39:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18227"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18227","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18227"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10941"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74973"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10941","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10941"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18227"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60479"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2115"},{"type":"tags","id":"3874"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"6066"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25428"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25433"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74973","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74973"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 60-year-old male had a liver function test repeated with his General Practitioner after discharge from the hospital for influenza. The alkaline phosphatase was still markedly raised which prompted further radiological investigations.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following would be used in treating Paget\u0027s disease of bone?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Bisphosphonates","Calcium supplements","Vitamin D supplements","Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs","Parathyroid hormone analogues"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBisphosphonates\u003C/strong\u003E are the first-line treatment for Paget\u0027s disease of bone. They work by inhibiting osteoclast-mediated bone resorption, thereby helping to normalise bone turnover and reduce symptoms such as bone pain and deformities. In this patient, bisphosphonates would be used to manage the increased bone turnover and alleviate symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECalcium supplements\u003C/strong\u003E are not used as a primary treatment for Paget\u0027s disease, although they may be prescribed alongside bisphosphonates to ensure adequate calcium levels, especially if dietary intake is insufficient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVitamin D supplements\u003C/strong\u003E are important for bone health but are not a specific treatment for Paget\u0027s disease. They may be used to prevent or treat vitamin D deficiency, which can occur in patients with high bone turnover.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs)\u003C/strong\u003E can be used to manage pain associated with Paget\u0027s disease but do not address the underlying bone pathology. They are an adjunctive treatment rather than a primary therapy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EParathyroid hormone analogues\u003C/strong\u003E are not used in the treatment of Paget\u0027s disease. They are typically used in osteoporosis to stimulate bone formation, which is not the primary issue in Paget\u0027s disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Bisphosphonates are the first-line treatment for Paget\u0027s disease of bone, as they help to regulate bone turnover and reduce symptoms.","Paget\u0027s disease is characterised by disorganised bone remodelling, leading to bone pain, deformities, and fractures.","Early treatment with bisphosphonates can prevent complications and improve quality of life in patients with Paget\u0027s disease."],"references":["Ralston SH. Bisphosphonates in the management of Paget\u0027s disease. Bone. 2020 Sep;138:115465. doi: 10.1016/j.bone.2020.115465. Epub 2020 Jun 5. PMID: 32512166.","Corral-Gudino L, Tan AJ, Del Pino-Montes J, Ralston SH. Bisphosphonates for Paget\u0027s disease of bone in adults. Cochrane Database Syst Rev. 2017 Dec 1;12(12):CD004956. doi: 10.1002/14651858.CD004956.pub3. PMID: 29192423; PMCID: PMC6486234.","Drake MT, Clarke BL, Khosla S. Bisphosphonates: mechanism of action and role in clinical practice. Mayo Clin Proc. 2008 Sep;83(9):1032-45. doi: 10.4065/83.9.1032. PMID: 18775204; PMCID: PMC2667901","Ganesan K, Goyal A, Roane D. Bisphosphonate. [Updated 2023 Jul 3]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK470248/","Khurana, I., Khurana, A., \u0026 Kowlgi, N. G. (2019). Textbook of Medical Physiology_-E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clarke B. Normal bone anatomy and physiology. Clin J Am Soc Nephrol. 2008 Nov;3 Suppl 3(Suppl 3):S131-9. doi: 10.2215/CJN.04151206. PMID: 18988698; PMCID: PMC3152283","Florencio-Silva R, Sasso GR, Sasso-Cerri E, Sim\u00f5es MJ, Cerri PS. Biology of Bone Tissue: Structure, Function, and Factors That Influence Bone Cells. Biomed Res Int. 2015;2015:421746. doi: 10.1155/2015/421746. Epub 2015 Jul 13. PMID: 26247020; PMCID: PMC4515490"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60479"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18227"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60479","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60479"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T12:59:47+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-